HEADWORD: Besnow
<hw>Be*snow"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Besnowed</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>bisnewen</ets>, AS. <ets>besn⟦imac⟧wan</ets>; pref. <ets>be-</ets>
+ <ets>sn⟦imac⟧wan</ets> to snow.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To scatter
like snow; to cover thick, as with snow flakes.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Gower.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To cover with snow; to whiten with snow, or as with
snow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

